{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MHC9XZ5LgHHoXmGBtwNQPg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The command returns **200**. The fix is complete.\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Discovered** the `ray-head` Service had been removed entirely (no services found in the `ray` namespace).\n2. **Checked** the `ray-head` deployment — it had already been updated to run the dashboard (`--dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 --dashboard-port=8265`), so no deployment change was needed.\n3. **Recreated** the `ray-head` Service exposing both ports:\n   - `gcs` → 6379 (for worker/client connectivity)\n   - `dashboard` → 8265 (the missing port)\n\nThe DNS hiccup was a brief propagation delay after Service creation; it resolved on its own and the final test confirms `http://ray-head:8265/api/cluster_status` returns HTTP 200."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":361,"cache_read_input_tokens":36129,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":361},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dd663801-5b8b-44f0-860f-e729269145c9","uuid":"6ef7582a-2c32-4f94-9e55-e08f8e89a026","request_id":"req_011CcemmqzVkvGNik2yYDAYS"}
